 Cambridge police, in East London, say on Tuesday they were notified about a shooting incident that happened at an East London Shopping Complex in Vincent in the afternoon. "It is alleged that a wheelchair-bound man shot another man, who was, apparently, trying to rob him of his money at an ATM," said police spokesperson, Capt Nkosikho Mzuku. "Police are investigating a case of robbery. "The suspect (44) was allegedly shot in the leg." He was later rushed to a local hospital for medical attention. "The suspect is due to appear in the East London Magistrates’ Court soon on charges of robbery," she said. 